+## Backend
+
+### Configuration
+
+**File**: `src/cddbs/config.py`
+
+All configuration is loaded from environment variables (with `.env` file support via `python-dotenv`).
+
+| Variable           | Default                                       | Description                          |
+|--------------------|-----------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------|
+| `SERPAPI_KEY`      | `None`                                        | SerpAPI key for news search          |
+| `GOOGLE_API_KEY`   | `None`                                        | Google Gemini API key                |
+| `GEMINI_MODEL`     | `gemini-2.5-flash`                            | Gemini model to use                  |
+| `ARTICLE_LIMIT`    | `3`                                           | Default max articles per analysis    |
+| `DATABASE_URL`     | `postgresql+psycopg2://admin:admin@db:5432/cddbs` | PostgreSQL connection string    |
+| `ALLOWED_ORIGINS`  | `*`                                           | CORS allowed origins (comma-separated)|
+| `DB_POOL_SIZE`     | `5`                                           | SQLAlchemy connection pool size      |
+| `DB_MAX_OVERFLOW`  | `10`                                          | Max overflow connections             |
+
+The `Settings` class automatically converts `postgres://` URLs (used by Render/Neon) to `postgresql://` for SQLAlchemy compatibility.
+
+### Database & Models
+
+**File**: `src/cddbs/database.py`
+
+- Uses `SQLAlchemy` with `declarative_base()`.
+- Connection pool configured with `pool_pre_ping=True` for connection health checks.
+- `init_db()` creates all tables on startup via `Base.metadata.create_all()` (no Alembic migrations required).
+
+**File**: `src/cddbs/models.py`
+
+Six ORM models across five tables:
