+## Frontend
+
+### Application Shell
+
+**File**: `frontend/src/App.tsx`
+
+The main layout consists of:
+
+1. **AppBar** (top): Search bar (collapsible on hover), "New Analysis" button, Settings icon.
+2. **Drawer** (left sidebar): Pin/hover behavior, navigation items, Test Guide and Leave Feedback buttons at the bottom.
+3. **Main content area**: Dashboard metrics grid (4 cards), Runs table (left), and Run detail + Status chart (right).
+4. **Dialogs**: NewAnalysisDialog, SettingsDialog, ReportViewDialog, KeyboardShortcutsDialog, TestGuideDialog, FeedbackDialog.
+
+Keyboard shortcuts (via `useKeyboardShortcuts`):
+- `Ctrl+K` — Focus search
+- `Ctrl+N` — New analysis
+- `Ctrl+R` — Refresh data
+- `Shift+?` — Show keyboard shortcuts
+- `Escape` — Close dialogs
+
+### State Management
+
+**File**: `frontend/src/store.ts`
+
+Redux Toolkit store with a single slice:
+
+**`runsSlice`** (`frontend/src/slices/runsSlice.ts`):
+- `selectedRunId: number | null` — Currently selected run for detail view
+- Action: `setSelectedRunId(id)`
+
+Most data fetching uses TanStack React Query, not Redux:
+- `useQuery(["runs"])` — Fetches run list with auto-refresh every 10s when runs are active
+- `useQuery(["run", id])` — Fetches individual run detail
+- `useQuery(["quality", id])` — Fetches quality scorecard
+- `useQuery(["narratives", id])` — Fetches narrative matches
+
+### API Client
+
+**File**: `frontend/src/api.ts`
+
+Axios instance configured with `baseURL: "/api"` (proxied to backend via Vite/Nginx).
+
+#### Functions
+
+| Function                | Method | Path                              | Returns              |
+|------------------------|--------|-----------------------------------|----------------------|
+| `wakeUpBackend()`      | GET    | `/health`                         | void (fire-and-forget)|
+| `createAnalysisRun()`  | POST   | `/analysis-runs`                  | `RunStatus`          |
+| `fetchRuns()`          | GET    | `/analysis-runs`                  | `RunStatus[]`        |
+| `fetchRun(id)`         | GET    | `/analysis-runs/{id}`             | `ReportResponse`     |
+| `fetchApiStatus()`     | GET    | `/api-status`                     | `ApiStatus`          |
+| `fetchQuality(id)`     | GET    | `/analysis-runs/{id}/quality`     | `QualityResponse`    |
+| `fetchNarrativeMatches(id)` | GET| `/analysis-runs/{id}/narratives` | `NarrativeMatchItem[]`|
+| `fetchNarrativesDb()`  | GET    | `/narratives`                     | `NarrativeInfo[]`    |
+| `submitFeedback()`     | POST   | `/feedback`                       | `FeedbackResponse`   |
+
+#### Key Types
+
+- `RunStatus` — Run list item (id, outlet, status, quality_score, narrative_count)
+- `ReportResponse` — Full report with articles and metadata
+- `QualityResponse` — Quality scorecard (dimensions, total, rating)
+- `NarrativeMatchItem` — Matched narrative (keywords, confidence, count)
+- `FeedbackPayload` — Feedback submission form data
+
+### Components Reference
+
+#### Core Components
+
+| Component                   | File                        | Description                                       |
+|----------------------------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
+| `RunsTable`                | `RunsTable.tsx`             | Sortable/filterable table of all analysis runs. Shows outlet, country, status, quality score, date. Row click selects run. |
+| `RunDetail`                | `RunDetail.tsx`             | Detail panel for selected run. Shows metadata, status, and "View Report" button. |
+| `NewAnalysisDialog`        | `NewAnalysisDialog.tsx`     | Modal form to create new analysis (outlet, URL, country, articles, date filter). Injects API keys from localStorage. |
+| `ReportViewDialog`         | `ReportViewDialog.tsx`      | Full-screen dialog showing the intelligence briefing. Left sidebar has articles, quality panel, narrative panel. Main area renders markdown briefing. |
+| `SettingsDialog`           | `SettingsDialog.tsx`        | API key configuration. Shows current key status. First-launch auto-open behavior. |
+
+#### Quality & Narrative Components
+
+| Component                   | File                        | Description                                       |
+|----------------------------|-----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
+| `QualityBadge`             | `QualityBadge.tsx`          | Displays quality score (X/70) with color-coded rating chip. |
+| `QualityRadarChart`        | `QualityRadarChart.tsx`     | Pure SVG radar chart showing all 7 quality dimensions. No external charting dependency. |
+| `NarrativeTags`            | `NarrativeTags.tsx`         | Color-coded narrative match pills with confidence badges and keyword chips on expand. |
