+
+---
+
+## Data Files
+
+### `known_narratives.json`
+
+Contains 18 known disinformation narratives organized by category:
+
+- **Anti-NATO**: NATO expansion aggression, NATO internal division
+- **Ukraine Revisionism**: Ukraine as failed state, Denazification justification, Crimea legitimacy
+- **Western Hypocrisy**: Western double standards, Democracy promotion as interference
+- **Multipolar World**: US decline narrative, BRICS rising power
+- **Historical Revisionism**: Soviet victory distortion, Cold War reframing
+- **Biological/Chemical**: US biolab conspiracy
+- **Energy/Economic**: Energy dependence leverage
+- **Information Warfare**: Russophobia narrative, Western media manipulation
+- **Territorial**: Arctic sovereignty claims
+- **Election Interference**: Democratic process undermining
+
+Each narrative has: `id`, `name`, `description`, `keywords[]`, `frequency`, `active`.
+
+### `briefing_v1.json`
+
+JSON schema reference for the expected briefing output structure. Used by the quality scorer to validate structural completeness.
+
+### `system_prompt_v1.3.txt`
+
+Enhanced system prompt for Gemini that defines the analyst persona, output format requirements, and analytical standards.
+
+---
+
+## Testing
+
+### Running Tests
+
+```bash
+# Run standalone tests (no DB required)
+pytest tests/test_quality.py tests/test_adapters.py tests/test_narratives.py tests/test_schema.py --noconftest -q
+
+# Run all tests (requires PostgreSQL)
+pytest -q
+
+# Run with coverage
+pytest --cov=src/cddbs -q
+```
+
+### Test Structure
+
+| Test File             | Tests | Requires DB | Description                            |
+|----------------------|-------|-------------|----------------------------------------|
+| `test_quality.py`    | 23    | No          | All 7 quality scorer dimensions + edge cases |
+| `test_adapters.py`   | 22    | No          | Twitter + Telegram adapter normalization |
+| `test_narratives.py` | 11    | No          | Narrative matching, thresholds, dedup   |
+| `test_schema.py`     | ~5    | No          | JSON schema validation (requires `jsonschema`) |
+| `test_api.py`        | ~10   | Yes         | API endpoint integration tests          |
+| `test_api_helpers.py`| ~5    | Yes         | API helper function tests               |
+| `test_database.py`   | ~3    | Yes         | Database connection and table creation  |
+| `test_fetch.py`      | ~5    | No          | Article fetcher (mock SerpAPI)          |
+| `test_models.py`     | ~5    | Yes         | ORM model CRUD operations               |
+| `test_orchestrator.py`| ~5   | Yes         | Pipeline orchestrator integration       |
+| `test_pipeline.py`   | ~5    | Yes         | End-to-end pipeline tests               |
+
+The `conftest.py` sets up a test database session. Use `--noconftest` for standalone tests that don't need DB.
+
+---
+
+## Deployment
+
+### Local Development (Docker Compose)
+
+```bash
+# Start all services
+docker compose up --build
+
+# Services:
+# - Frontend: http://localhost:5173
+# - Backend:  http://localhost:8000
+# - Database: localhost:5432
+# - API Docs: http://localhost:8000/docs
+```
+
+### Production (Render)
+
+The `render.yaml` blueprint defines two web services and a database:
+
+1. **cddbs-api** (Backend)
+   - Docker build from root `Dockerfile`
+   - Health check: `/health`
+   - Environment: `DATABASE_URL` from Neon, `ALLOWED_ORIGINS=*`
+   - Pool settings: `DB_POOL_SIZE=2`, `DB_MAX_OVERFLOW=3` (free tier)
+
+2. **cddbs-frontend** (Frontend)
+   - Docker build from `frontend/Dockerfile`
+   - Nginx serves static build + proxies `/api` to backend
+
+3. **cddbs-db** (Database)
+   - Neon PostgreSQL (free tier)
+
+### Docker Images
+
+**Backend** (`Dockerfile`):
+```dockerfile
+FROM python:3.11-slim
+WORKDIR /app
+COPY requirements.txt /app/requirements.txt
+RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r /app/requirements.txt
+COPY src /app/src
+ENV PYTHONPATH=/app
+CMD ["uvicorn", "src.cddbs.api.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
+```
+
+**Frontend** (`frontend/Dockerfile`): Multi-stage build → Nginx serving static files.
+
